HEADWORD: Humoralism
<hw>Hu"mor*al*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The state or quality of being humoral.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The doctrine that diseases proceed
from the humors; humorism.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Humoralist</ent>⟦br⟧
